node.text:
Pink iced buns are on the blog today! The recipe uses the exact same dough as my burger buns so you can mix and match a wee bit. Last night I made 6 burger buns for dinner then turned the rest into 6 mini iced buns for dessert. I’ve talked about how good a versatile base recipe is a lot before but it truly is the best - nail down one dough technique and your options are almost endless. Recipe link is in my profile along with loads of recipe notes etc as always 💕💕💕
.
.
.
.
.

node.text: There’s a new recipe up on @kana.goods today - these maple glazed crullers! Cutting parchment paper squares is one of my least favorite jobs in the kitchen, so piping these crullers onto Kana’s 6” parchment paper circles is a total game changer. I finished these crullers with a maple glaze but you can finish them any way that you like! Get the recipe on Kana’s website via the link in my profile. They are also having a wee celebration 20% off sale on their Milo cast iron cookware. My code CLOUDYKITCHEN10 works in conjunction with this! Their Dutch oven is amazing for deep frying and you could whisk up the maple glaze in their mini dutch oven which is just so, so cute! #Sponsored #GoodsMadeBetter

node.text:
These vegan banana muffins are live on my site! Recipe courtesy of @flourish_bakeshop who I texted asking if she had a recipe then it was so good I just asked if I could put it on my site because there wasn’t anything I could do to it to make it better. These are 🔥 and the recipe is so, so easy! It also makes six, which to me, is the perfect amount of muffins. Link is in my bio! Next up is Chelsea’s sourdough focaccia once I revive my starter 😂🥰❤️
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
I know some people are team sourdough during lockdown but I am also team focaccia (sourdough focaccia is coming as soon as I revive my starter!). If you need a wee satisfying project I got you. This one has a garlic oil on it but you could also drown it in garlic butter as soon as it comes out of the oven (use the garlic butter recipe from my garlic knots) or leave the garlic out all together and just make a plain focaccia! I tested this every which way and the best part is you can make a batch of dough and leave it in the fridge for a few days and pull a bit off and bake up as needed. Notes in the recipe for small batching this one! Link is in my  bio :) 
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
Swipe to bake ✨ (ad) there’s a new recipe on the blog today for this blueberry balsamic crostata! (I’m calling it a crostata as it’s in the style of one but it’s also a tart / pie hybrid?) regardless of what you call it it’s SO good. I developed this months ago and have been so excited to share! There’s a flaky crust and a balsamic berry filling made with my fave @filippoberio_us balsamic vinegar. The filling works perfectly with both fresh and frozen fruit if berries aren’t in season where you are! And pie crust + tart pan = most epic filling to crust ratio! This one is so, so good, I hope you enjoy 💕 recipe is linked in my bio! #filippoberio #sponsored 
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
These twisty cinnamon buns are on the blog today! They look super fancy but the process is really easy - it’s just a rolled up braid. These are made with my small batch no mixer brioche, which is my current fave (it’s just a half batch of my regular dough). These wee buns are so soft, and just so, so good. Link is in my bio 💕
.
.
.
.
.

node.text: Just in case you were wondering… this method for lining a 9x13 works perfectly on tiny sheet pans using tiny parchment paper. It’s my fave way to line a pan. Cut slits about in line with the sides and about as deep as the pan, then push down and arrange the strips. I grease my pan first to make it easy, you don’t have to if you don’t want to. Tiny sheet cakes for the win. 💕😍 #lifehacks #oddlysatisfying #bakingtips

node.text:
Pizza pretzels are on the blog today! I scaled back my recipe and tweaked the dough formula a wee bit so this makes 6 super chewy, cheesy pizza pretzels. Leave the pepperoni off if you want, add in other stuff, you do you. All the details including info about TINY PEPPERONI are on the blog post, link in my bio!
